[Jim Alexander passed on the following information from Craig Carter &
Norman Ronald, Texas Veterinary Diagnostic Laboratory:
Carter & Ronald are working on a computer based diagnostic program for
human infectious diseases (it doesn't address environmental problems like
lead which should still be ruled out). His program's results indicated
listeriosis as the highest probability and the presence of CNS symptoms
indicate an urgency to obtain proper treatment if listeriosis is the
etiologic agent.
Their addresses are: <cncarter@tvmdl.tamu.edu> and <n-ronald@tvmdl.tamu.edu>
[Thanks Craig & Norman. - Mod.MHJ
